==English==

===Noun===

{{en-noun}}

# A type of formula-based [[cliché]] which uses an old [[idiom]] in a new context, especially in journalism.
#:''if Eskimos have N words for snow, X surely have Y words for Z''
#:''X is the new Y''

===Etymology===
The term was coined by [http://www.csun.edu/~dgw61315/index.html Glen Whitman] in an email sent on 2004-01-15 [http://itre.cis.upenn.edu/~myl/languagelog/archives/000350.html] in response to the following request from Geoffrey Pullum on the blog, Language Log:
"the thing we need a name for is a multi-use, customizable, instantly recognizable, time-worn, quoted or misquoted phrase or sentence that can be used in an entirely open array of different jokey variants by lazy journalists and writers."[http://itre.cis.upenn.edu/~myl/languagelog/archives/000061.html]

